-- Sri Lanka's Union Bank <UNIO.CM> sells 70 pct stake to TPG for $113 mln 
-- By Shihar Aneez amd Ranga Sirilal
-- Thu Aug 14, 2014 05:49AM EDT
-- None



COLOMBO, Aug 14 (Reuters) - Sri Lanka's Union Bank of Colombo PLC <UNIO.CM> on Thursday said it had agreed to sell a 70 percent stake for $113 million to a subsidiary of TPG Capital Management LP.

Culture Financial Holdings Ltd, an affiliate of TPG, will invest up to about $113 million in Union Bank of Colombo through a combination of primary and secondary shares, the bank said in a statement to the Colombo Stock Exchange.